name: CommonProceduresRequiringPreProceduralPCI
title: Common Procedures Requiring Pre Procedural PCI
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This comprehensive set of codes includes frequent procedures for which a PCI is performed in preparation for the procedure (e.g., valve procedures, organ transplants).),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who receive select procedures for which a PCI may be required in preparation for and prior to the procedure (e.g., patients with aortic stenosis undergoing PCI prior to transcatheter aortic valve replacement [TAVR]).),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes ICD-10-PCS/CPT/SNOMED-CT codes that indicate procedures for which a PCI is performed in preparation for the procedure (e.g., valve procedures, organ transplants).),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes ICD-10-PCS/CPT/SNOMED-CT codes that do not indicate procedures for which a PCI is performed in preparation for the procedure (e.g., valve procedures, organ transplants).)
